        <updateDate>2008-04-30T19:02:28Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Congressional Leadership in Communities Resolution of 2008 - Permits Members of the House of Representatives to: (1) sponsor or conduct academic and community service competitions among elementary and secondary school students in their Congressional districts; and (2) allow charitable organizations to use their office facilities in support of charitable or educational purposes, so long as such use does not interfere with regular office operations.</p> <p>Considers amounts Members spend for the academic and community service competitions to be amounts spent in support of their official and representational duties.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
